WEBVTT

00:00.252 --> 00:03.254
The Carmichael Show is taped in
front of a live studio audience.

00:03.469 --> 00:06.610
Hey, Dad, Donald Trump is the president

00:06.611 --> 00:08.145
of the United States.

00:08.213 --> 00:10.781
That's crazy, right?

00:10.849 --> 00:12.716
I mean, it still looks like an ad

00:12.817 --> 00:15.052
for <i>The Apprentice</i> to me.

00:15.153 --> 00:16.453
Hey, Cordell.

00:16.521 --> 00:20.123
Tony... I see that salt and pepper

00:20.191 --> 00:21.658
in your hair, man.

00:21.726 --> 00:22.766
You gettin' up there, boy.

00:22.827 --> 00:24.394
Dad, how often do you come

00:24.495 --> 00:25.829
to this army recruiting center?

00:25.897 --> 00:27.308
Well, I come here about once a week.

00:27.332 --> 00:28.432
I like to drop off doughnuts,

00:28.499 --> 00:29.766
show my appreciation.

00:29.834 --> 00:31.768
You haven't taken Mom
on a date in six months,

00:31.836 --> 00:34.271
and you come here once a week?

00:34.339 --> 00:36.306
I bring your mama doughnuts, too.

00:38.176 --> 00:40.477
Wait a minute, is that Kevin Wilson?

00:40.545 --> 00:41.865
I didn't know he joined the army.

00:42.580 --> 00:43.357
Oh, you mean that kid
that lived down the block?

00:43.381 --> 00:45.616
Well, so it is.

00:45.683 --> 00:46.817
Well, give him a doughnut

00:46.885 --> 00:48.185
and thank him for his service.

00:48.286 --> 00:51.054
No. I don't like Kevin Wilson.

00:51.155 --> 00:52.289
None of us do.

00:52.357 --> 00:53.701
He's an arrogant bastard who used to

00:53.725 --> 00:54.805
beat Bobby up all the time.

00:54.859 --> 00:56.560
Okay, come on, man, I mean,

00:56.661 --> 00:58.295
we scrapped a few times here and there.

00:58.363 --> 00:59.840
You know, it was mostly fifty-fifty...

00:59.864 --> 01:00.941
he'll win some, and I'll win some.

01:00.965 --> 01:03.333
Oh, no, Bobby, you never won.

01:03.401 --> 01:04.678
Remember, you had to transfer schools

01:04.702 --> 01:05.836
just to get him to stop.

01:05.904 --> 01:08.338
Yeah, he did used to whup your ass.

01:08.406 --> 01:11.308
Well, I'm sure he's changed now.

01:11.376 --> 01:13.076
They're not gonna let some violent man

01:13.177 --> 01:15.345
who likes to bully
other people into the army.

01:15.413 --> 01:16.790
What are you talking about, Dad?
That has to be, like,

01:16.814 --> 01:19.216
75% of the army.

01:19.317 --> 01:21.318
He got my friend Stacy pregnant

01:21.386 --> 01:23.553
and has done nothing
to help raise that kid.

01:23.655 --> 01:26.189
He used to wear his sunglasses
on the back of his head.

01:26.257 --> 01:27.658
He drinks Monster Energy drinks.

01:27.725 --> 01:29.660
The man's a terrible person,
case closed.

01:29.727 --> 01:31.361
Yeah, well, he's a troop now.

01:31.429 --> 01:32.729
And those uniforms, they're like

01:32.830 --> 01:34.364
a cloak of forgiveness.

01:34.432 --> 01:36.333
Even the worst troop is better

01:36.401 --> 01:37.701
than the greatest civilian.

01:37.769 --> 01:39.703
If I were walking home tonight

01:39.771 --> 01:41.505
and I got jumped by a troop,

01:41.572 --> 01:44.708
I would be thankful I gave
him the extra training.

01:44.776 --> 01:46.343
Kevin.

01:46.411 --> 01:48.178
Mr. Carmichael.

01:50.581 --> 01:51.882
So, when'd you join the army?

01:51.950 --> 01:53.717
Just finished basic training last week.

01:53.785 --> 01:56.219
- Hey, Bobby.
- Hey, man. All right, quit playing.

01:58.532 --> 02:01.100
- Hey, Jerrod.
- Kevin.

02:01.201 --> 02:03.035
Thank you for your service.

02:03.103 --> 02:06.906
Yeah, yeah, yeah, thank
you for your service.

02:06.974 --> 02:08.184
I'm not thanking you for your service.

02:08.208 --> 02:10.776
You used to beat my brother up.

02:10.877 --> 02:13.045
This guy? We just always
used to have fun.

02:13.113 --> 02:14.447
No, you didn't.

02:14.548 --> 02:17.717
Look at his face;
he is terrified right now.

02:17.784 --> 02:21.787
No, I'm not. I'm cool.

02:21.889 --> 02:24.724
Jerrod, quit bringing up old bidness.

02:24.791 --> 02:28.761
Now, Kevin, I am proud of the
man that you have become.

02:28.829 --> 02:30.796
And we all know
you're gonna go out there

02:30.898 --> 02:33.599
and kill all the bad hombres
and make us proud.

02:35.469 --> 02:36.903
Thank you, Mr. Carmichael.

02:36.970 --> 02:38.571
You know, I just woke up one morning

02:38.639 --> 02:40.773
and felt there was a greater
calling for my life.

02:40.841 --> 02:43.809
I decided to join something
bigger than myself.

02:43.911 --> 02:45.778
I wake up before the sun rises

02:45.846 --> 02:47.991
just to get to work protecting
this country from threats

02:48.015 --> 02:49.615
you can't even imagine.

02:49.683 --> 02:51.584
You just completed basic training.

02:51.652 --> 02:54.954
You learned how to do
sit-ups and make the bed.

02:55.022 --> 02:57.623
I don't expect you to understand

02:57.691 --> 03:00.126
the type of responsibility
this takes, Jerrod,

03:00.194 --> 03:01.827
but you don't have to.

03:01.929 --> 03:04.096
Because there will always
be people like me

03:04.164 --> 03:05.932
to take care of people like you.

03:05.999 --> 03:08.935
Kevin, what's the real
reason you joined the army?

03:09.002 --> 03:11.938
Was it the easiest way to get
respect you don't deserve,

03:12.005 --> 03:13.683
or are you just trying
to avoid fatherhood?

03:13.707 --> 03:15.147
You don't have to answer him, Kevin.

03:15.175 --> 03:18.144
He is just a scrawny, rude civilian.

03:19.680 --> 03:21.614
It's cool, Mr. Carmichael.

03:21.682 --> 03:23.193
Jerrod, for starters, I joined because

03:23.217 --> 03:25.651
I love my country. Loves his country.

03:26.787 --> 03:28.654
And I wanted to give something back.

03:28.722 --> 03:29.789
Give something back.

03:29.856 --> 03:31.524
You know, make a sacrifice.

03:31.625 --> 03:34.160
Sacrifice!

03:34.228 --> 03:36.996
Daddy, it's like you're his hype man.

03:38.031 --> 03:40.800
Jerrod, no more disrespecting Kevin.

03:40.867 --> 03:42.501
Kevin is a good soldier

03:42.569 --> 03:44.704
on his way to achieving greatness.

03:44.805 --> 03:46.505
Now, thank him for his service

03:46.573 --> 03:48.474
and give this man a doughnut.

03:48.542 --> 03:50.042
Fine.

03:50.143 --> 03:53.813
Kevin, thank you for your service,

03:53.880 --> 03:56.649
you arrogant deadbeat dad.

03:56.717 --> 03:58.651
Hmm, um,

03:58.719 --> 04:01.153
cinnamon sugar or jelly?

